The paper deals with the problem of recovering missing state variable observations in electricity distribution systems. This problem is related to control and optimization of power systems, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The proposed method involves matrix completion and Bayesian estimation, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also mentions the use of prior knowledge, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
